data:
Background and objectives 

The project "Honing of Skills in International Apprenticeship (HOSIA)" by Hiiumaa Vocational School is a tool for enhancing primary areas of our main activities, pedagogical concept and goals for International cooperation as outlined in our Development Plan.  

This includes:

- being a trusted partner for employers; 
- creating a best possible environment for our students for their studies and development as a member of society; 
- to ensure international cooperation options in all fields of study to support and enrich the content and best practices of vocational education; to exchange knowledge and expertise, and increase the mobility of both students and professionals. 

The objectives for quality assurance are:

- Our school has an efficient placement training system to be applied in close cooperation with students and employers for the optimal achievement of learning outcomes;
- Vocational education is closely engaged with employment market;
- Mobility of vocational students has increased;
- Increased attractiveness of vocational education

This project has one focus connected to our main activities: development and elaboration of placement training system of our school. Coinciding with this Student Mobility project is the development of placement training system for students as an essential part of outcome-based curricula. Student Mobility programme has introduced an exemplary model to be used also for domestic placements.

Students’ development goals

Students who have undergone international placement training shall:
- appreciate the role of placement training for achieving required professional competence;
- have acquired necessary competence and are more competitive on the job market;
- have put their studies on test in international environment and analysed the process;
- have better language skills.

Goals of international cooperation

- The cooperation between Hiiumaa Vocational School and our international partners in the fields of horticulture and construction is maintained and functioning well.
- International partners have been selected purposefully to meet training needs of required competencies of respective students;
- International cooperation facilitates exchange of knowledge and expertise in vocational fields of study of horticulture and construction.
- We maintain and develop our placement partnership network so that we have sufficient knowledge of employer’s background, and placement options and conditions while offering a wide variety to choose from for our students. This includes cooperation with British, Norwegian and Dutch partners.

This project engages 18 students and recent graduates of horticulture and construction fields of study in Hiiumaa Vocational School. In between September 2017 and July 2018, the flowing international placements will take place:

- 4 florists at Eduelta College in the Netherlands
- 6 restorers of stone and timber buildings at Hå Gamle Prestegard in Norway
- 4 gardeners and landscape gardeners at Edudelta College in the Netherlands
- 4 restorers of stone and timber buildings at Great Yarmouth Preservation Trust in the UK
